{"worksheets":[{"cells":[{"metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#SPOC and Sarek Mandelbrot sample"},{"metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Open SPOC, Kirc and Dom HTML modules."},{"metadata":{},"input":"open Spoc;;\nopen Kirc;;\nopen Dom_html","cell_type":"code","outputs":[],"language":"python","collapsed":false},{"metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*int and float refs* can be accessed from Sarek Kernels.\n\nHere **width, height and max_iter** are globals shared between the host code and the sarek kernel"},{"metadata":{},"input":"let width = ref 512l;;\nlet height = ref 512l;;\nlet max_iter  = ref 50l;;","cell_type":"code","outputs":[],"language":"python","collapsed":false},{"metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**mandelbrot** is our GPGPU kernel\n\nIt's written with Sarek, a DSL dedicated to GPGPU kernels embedded into OCaml.\n\n*TODO : describe kernel*"},{"metadata":{},"input":"let mandelbrot = kern img -> \n  let open Std in\n  let y = thread_idx_y + (block_idx_y * block_dim_y) in\n  let x = thread_idx_x + (block_idx_x * block_dim_x) in\n  if (y < !height) && (x < !width) then\n     begin  \n       let x0 = x  in\n       let y0 = y  in\n       let mutable cpt = 0 in \n       let mutable x1 = 0. in\n       let mutable y1 = 0. in\n       let mutable x2 = 0. in\n       let mutable y2 = 0. in\n       let a = 4. *. ((float x0) /. (float !width))   -. 2. in\n       let b = 4. *. ((float y0) /. (float !height)) -. 2. in\n\n       let mutable norm = x1 *. x1 +. y1 *. y1\n       in\n       while ((cpt < !max_iter) && (norm <=. 4.)) do\n         cpt := (cpt + 1);\n         x2 := (x1 *. x1) -. (y1 *. y1) +. a;\n         y2 :=  (2. *. x1 *. y1 ) +. b;\n         x1 := x2;\n         y1 := y2;\n         norm := (x1 *. x1 ) +. ( y1 *. y1);\n       done;\n       img.[<y * !width + x>] <- cpt\n     end","cell_type":"code","outputs":[],"language":"python","collapsed":false},{"metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*TODO: describe host code*"},{"metadata":{},"input":"let color n = \n  if n =  !max_iter then\n    (196, 200, 200)\n  else \n    let f n = \n      let n = Int32.to_int n in\n      let i = float n in \n      int_of_float (255. *. (0.5 +. 0.5 *. sin(i *. 0.1))) in\n    ((f (Int32.add n 32l)),  (f(Int32.add n 16l)),  (f n))\n\n\nlet compute devid devs data imageData c= \n  let dev = devs.(devid) in\n  Printf.printf \"Will use device : %s!\"\n    (dev).Spoc.Devices.general_info.Spoc.Devices.name;\n  let gpu_vect = Spoc.Vector.create Vector.int32 ((Int32.to_int !width) * (Int32.to_int !height))\n  in\n  Random.self_init ();\n\n  let threadsPerBlock = match dev.Devices.specific_info with\n    | Devices.OpenCLInfo clI -> \n      (match clI.Devices.device_type with\n      | Devices.CL_DEVICE_TYPE_CPU -> 1\n      | _  ->   16)\n    | _  -> 16  in\n  let blocksPerGridx =\n    ((Int32.to_int !width) + (threadsPerBlock) -1) / (threadsPerBlock) in\n  let blocksPerGridy =\n    ((Int32.to_int !height) + (threadsPerBlock) -1) / (threadsPerBlock) in\n  let block = {Spoc.Kernel.blockX = threadsPerBlock;\n         Spoc.Kernel.blockY = threadsPerBlock;\n            Spoc.Kernel.blockZ = 1}\n  and grid= {Spoc.Kernel.gridX = blocksPerGridx;\n       Spoc.Kernel.gridY = blocksPerGridy;\n            Spoc.Kernel.gridZ = 1} in\n\n     Kirc.run mandelbrot (gpu_vect) (block,grid) 0 dev;\n      for i = 0 to Vector.length gpu_vect - 1 do\n        let t = gpu_vect.[<i>] in \n        let r,g,b = (color t) in \n        pixel_set data (i*4) r; \n        pixel_set data (i*4+1) g; \n        pixel_set data (i*4+2) b; \n        pixel_set data (i*4+3) 255; \n      done;\n  c##putImageData (imageData, 0., 0.);\n;;","cell_type":"code","outputs":[],"language":"python","collapsed":false},{"metadata":{},"input":"let error f = Printf.ksprintf (fun s -> Firebug.console##error (Js.string s); failwith s) f\n\nlet go _ =\nignore (\n    let canvas =   Js.Opt.get\n        (Js.Opt.bind ( Dom_html.document##getElementById(\"canvas\") )\n            Dom_html.CoerceTo.canvas)\n        (fun () -> error \"can't find canvas element canvas\") in\n    \n    let c = canvas##getContext (Dom_html._2d_) in\n    let devs =\n        Devices.init ~only:Devices.OpenCL () in      \n        ignore(Kirc.gen ~only:Devices.OpenCL\n        mandelbrot);\n    let imageData = c##getImageData (0., 0., (Int32.to_float !width), (Int32.to_float !height)) in\n    let data = imageData##data in\n    \n     compute 0 devs data imageData c;\n    \n    Js._true)\n\n(*let _ =   window##onload <- handler go *) ","cell_type":"code","outputs":[],"language":"python","collapsed":false},{"metadata":{},"input":"go ()","cell_type":"code","outputs":[],"language":"python","collapsed":true},{"metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"This cell embedded that canvas element to which we render\n\n<canvas id=\"canvas\" height=\"512\" width=\"512\"></canvas>"}],"metadata":{}}],"metadata":{"name":"","language":"ocaml"}}